  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">An effective monopole action is derived from vacuum configurations after abelian projection in the maximally abelian gauge in $SU(2)$ QCD. Entropy dominance over energy of monopole loops is seen on the renormalized lattice with the spacing $b>b_c\simeq 5.2\times10~{-3} \Lambda_L~{-1}$ when the physical volume of the system is large enough. QCD confinement may be interpreted as the (dual) Meissner effect due to the monopole condensation.</subfield>
  </datafield>
